groups.label: Please advise nurses if you have any questions or concerns prior to vaccination
Before receiving the immunisation, please read and answer the following questions:
NOTE: Please ask your Doctor/ Nurse questions about this information or any matter relating to immunisation before the immunisation is given.
All sections must be completed before vaccination can begin
Have you had a severe reaction following any immunisation?
Are you currently unwell or suffering from a high temperature?
Do you have a bleeding disorder?
Do you have a chronic Illness?
Do you have a past history of Guillain-Barre` Syndrome? (Symmetrical paralysis of limbs/immune response affecting nerves)

Do you have a disease which lowers the bodys defense system (immunity) ie. Leukemia, Cancer, HIV/AIDS Or are you having treatment which lowers the bodys defense system (immunity) such as oral steroid medicines such as Cortisone and prednisone, radiotherapy, chemotherapy)
Women only: Is there a possibility that you could be pregnant?
Have you had any immunisations in the past month?
Have you had an injection of immunoglobulin (antibodies)
Have you received any blood products or had a blood transfusion within the past year?
Before any vaccination takes place, the immunisation service provider will ask you
Did you understand the information provided to you about the immunisation?
Do you need more information to decide whether to proceed?
By signing this form that I consent to the vaccination to be administered by the health personnel from AMC360.
Parent or care givers name and signature:
